    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-23T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-23T03:00:00-05:00" n="900"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.801 Search/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Adams</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-23T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 23, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—7:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. My 125, December 12, 1 p.m. No representations have been made by the Chinese
                    authorities and I am inclined to believe that none will be made since the troops
                    who were put off the <hi rend="italic">Ifung</hi> have left this area.</p>
                <p>Legation and Nanking informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
